comment: Baynes (DET) sets the screen on Dinwiddie (BKN) without giving him room to avoid the contact.
Baynes (DET) makes marginal contact with Lopez (BKN) that does not affect his drive to the basket and shot attempt.
[Observable in enhanced video] Morris (DET) moves his pivot foot.
Lopez (BKN) legally contests Morris' (DET) jump shot attempt. Any "high-five" contact after the release is considered incidental.
Morris (DET) does not dislodge LeVert (BKN) from his legal guarding position.
Morris (DET) makes contact to LeVert's (BKN) arm that affects his driving shot attempt.
[Observable in enhanced video] Harris (DET) moves his pivot foot at the start of his dribble.
Baynes (DET) makes incidental contact with LeVert (BKN) that does not affect his SQBR.
Smith (DET) makes contact to Whitehead's (BKN) wrist that affects his jump shot attempt and follow-through.
Dinwiddie (BKN) legally contests Morris' (DET) jump shot attempt.
Whitehead (BKN) legally contests Harris' (DET) shot attempt.
RATR shows Baynes (DET) make contact to Lopez' (BKN) body that affects his drive to the basket and shot attempt.
After communicating with the Replay Center, the ruling on the floor that Lopez (BKN) released his field goal attempt prior to the game clock expiring is confirmed.
